The paper deals with the problem of controlling an autonomous surface vehicle to follow a path while avoiding obstacles, which is a classic problem in robotics and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses deep reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of a state-of-the-art algorithm for continuous control tasks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of dual-objective optimization, which involves balancing two competing objectives, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper uses rangefinder sensors for obstacle detection, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
